{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:31:32.339660+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"apply_migrations.sh applies files in wrong order on filesystems with case-folding\",\"body\":\"Hi — I think I found an ordering bug in `scripts/apply_migrations.sh`.\\n\\nOn my workstation (macOS, default APFS, `LC_COLLATE=en_US.UTF-8`), running `./scripts/apply_migrations.sh` from a fresh checkout sometimes applies `003_add_session_index.sql` before `002_create_sessions.sql`. That fails because the index targets a table that hasn\\u0026#39;t been created yet.\\n\\nMy best guess: the script relies on `for f in migrations/*.sql; do` which uses shell glob expansion, and APFS being case-insensitive plus a non-C locale messes with the sort order in zsh on some Apple builds.\\n\\nReproducer:\\n  1. Fresh checkout\\n  2. docker compose up -d\\n  3. ./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\\n\\nResult: psql complains \\u0026#34;relation \\\\\\u0026#34;sessions\\\\\\u0026#34; does not exist\\u0026#34; while applying 003.\\n\\nWorkaround I\\u0026#39;m using locally: replace the loop with\\n  `for f in $(ls migrations/*.sql | sort); do`\\n\\nHappy to send a PR if a sorted-explicit loop is acceptable.\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T00:49:36Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T00:49:36Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMDo0OTozNlrPAAAAAQwnhUo=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMDo0OTozNlrPAAAAAQwnhUo=\"}}", "id": "lc_82f3992e-c968-4201-a759-7dc280287dd0"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "08e520de-11cd-4e7e-bc55-68f8b08c84f0", "tool_call_id": "call_40dc1e27aa8e4584b858da1a", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
